definition.value: A member of the class of indolones that is 3,5-dihydro-2H-indole substituted by an oxo group at position 5 and a hydroxy group at position 6.
An  indolylmethylglucosinolic acid that is glucobrassicin bearing a methoxy substituent at position 4 on the indole ring.

An L-asparagine derivative that is L-asparagine in which the amino group undergoes formal consensation with the carboxy group of benzoic acid and in which the carboxy OH group is replaced by a (4-nitrophenyl)amino group. It is an asparaginyl endopeptidase substrate.

A member of the class of indoledione that is 2,3,5,6-tetrahydro-1H-indole carrying oxo groups at positions 5 and 6; major microspecies at pH 7.3. It is an endogenous compound formed during dopamine oxidation and can induce neurotoxicity under certain aberrant conditions and induce Parkinson-like syndrome.
A member of the class of hydroquinones that is benzene-1,4-diol carrying four methyl groups at positions 2, 3, 5 and 6.
A benzoate that is the conjugate base of 4-formylbenzoic acid arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
